\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {10}{\ignorespaces First-generation extinction profile based on DES Y1 redMaGiC catalogs and my terrible 2018 code. From left to right: background galaxy extinction profiles calculated in 2, 10, and 20 redshift bins. As the number of redshift bins increases, the slope of the extinction profile appears to get steeper. The raw signal is shown in orange, while the random-corrected signal is shown in blue. The green line shows an incorrectly scaled version of the M\'{e}nard 2010 extinction profile.}}{15}{figure.10}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:old}{{10}{15}{First-generation extinction profile based on DES Y1 redMaGiC catalogs and my terrible 2018 code. From left to right: background galaxy extinction profiles calculated in 2, 10, and 20 redshift bins. As the number of redshift bins increases, the slope of the extinction profile appears to get steeper. The raw signal is shown in orange, while the random-corrected signal is shown in blue. The green line shows an incorrectly scaled version of the M\'{e}nard 2010 extinction profile}{figure.10}{}}
